title: Year-Round Sunshine Levels
description: The visualization aims to highlight which city consistently experiences the highest average sunshine hours throughout the year, which happened to be San Diego. I created a narrative that emphasizes San Diego's distinct advantage in providing sunny weather, making it an ideal destination for travelers seeking consistent sunshine.

title: Recipe Analysis Project
description: As an undergraduate student with a packed schedule, cooking is both a creative outlet, a balancing act, and an opportunity to not have dining hall meals. When I cook, time is often of the essence, and the number of steps in a recipe can determine whether a meal is quick and satisfying or a time-consuming challenge. With this in mind, this report delves into how the complexity and duration of recipes might influence ratings of recipes, particularly for those who, like me, juggle academics, commitments, and the desire for homemade meals.

title: DUI Analysis Project
description: Our group worked on a data analysis to understand the impact of DUI on car crash severity and to identify age-specific trends in DUI-related collisions in Los Angeles. We leveraged the detailed LA Traffic Collision dataset, which through its MO Codes, enabled us to ascertain patterns in crash severity and victim demographics. Our findings revealed that DUI-related accidents lead to higher injury levels compared to non-DUI incidents and disproportionately affect individuals within the 20-25 and 35-50 age brackets. These insights underscore the pressing need for targeted interventions to mitigate the risks of DUI, particularly among these vulnerable age groups, and enhance community safety.

title: Gradebook
description: In this project, I worked with the gradebook for CSD 18, a fictional data science course with 535 students co-taught by Professors Yutian and Dylan. I helped Professors Yutian and Dylan compute the total course grade for every student in their course and analyze their students' performances throughout the quarter.

title: Loan Applications
description: In this project, I explored how various borrower characteristics are related to one another, in an attempt to better understand the complexity behind loans. It's important to keep in mind, that this dataset only contains information about actually approved loans, not all loan applications.

title: Language Models
description: In this project, I buildt my own language models, using publicly-available books found on Project Gutenberg.

title: Image Processing App
description: Made a basic image processing app in DSC 20 using a KNN classifier.

title: Relationships and Trends between Compensation, Education, and Technology for Data Science Careers
description: As students who aspire to use data science in our future careers, we decided to analyze the dataset that best suited our interests and could answer some of our personal questions.

title: UCSD Admissions Project/Analysis
description: In this project, I took a look at UC San Diego's undergraduate admissions numbers for the class of first-year students (i.e. not transfers) that entered in Fall 2022. The data comes directly from the University of California's Information Center.
